	<title>A1. Word Meanings</title>
	<terms>
		<item>
			<title>Block</title>
			<p>A group of contiguous (filled) cells.
			</p>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>Block extent</title>
			<p>The minimum number of cells required to accomodate the blocks (with one empty space between each).
			</p>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>Cell</title>
			<p>Smallest square in the grid.  Can either be coloured as filled, empty or unknown
			</p>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>Clue</title>
			<p>The set of numbers that indicate the pattern of filled cells in a row/column (see <link xref="howtoplay"/>)
			</p>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>Freedom</title>
			<p>How much room for manoeuvre there is in a row/column.  The difference between the total number of cells in the row/column and the block extent.
			</p>
		</item>

		<item>
		<title>Region</title>
			<p>A row or column or a length of contiguous cells within a row or column</p>
		</item>

		<item>
		<title>Range (of a block)</title>
			<p>The region within which the block must be placed</p>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>Design Grid</title>
			<p>The rectangular array of cells that holds the solution to the puzzle or on which you can draw your own puzzle
			</p>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>Working Grid</title>
			<p>The rectangular array of cells that holds your working when trying to solve a puzzle
			</p>
		</item>

		<item>
			<title>Guide Grid</title>
			<p>A grid of lines outlining the borders of the cells
			</p>
		</item>

	</terms>
